<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFED293DF8D9FED20DEC4ECD" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFED293DF8D9FED20DEC4ECD" blockId="3.[151,1437,295,394]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
In the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DF967FEDD0DB14E05" authorityName="Harring" authorityYear="1913" box="[297,445,295,321]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DF967FEDD0DB14E05" box="[297,445,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Philodinavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only two species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DFAD9FED20F254E05" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[663,809,295,321]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DFAD9FED20F254E05" box="[663,809,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DFB2FFED20FFC4E05" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[865,1008,296,321]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DFB2FFED20FFC4E05" box="[865,1008,296,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been known to the world before the present study. 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DF92EFEB10E7C4E21" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[352,624,331,357]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DF92EFEB10E7C4E21" box="[352,624,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Philodinavus paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been newly reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F3377639FFED293DFB85FEB608034E22" box="[971,1039,332,358]" name="South Korea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Korea</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B58FFED293DFC76FEB109174E21" author="Song, M. O. &amp; Kim, W." box="[1080,1307,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="91 - 101" refId="ref6980" refString="Song, M. O. &amp; Kim, W. (2000) Bdelloid rotifers from Korea. Hydrobiologia, 439, 91 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1004181414535" type="journal article" year="2000">Song &amp; Kim (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, which was the first Asian record as well.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A6522FFED293DF8D9FE2109914D8C" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="key">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFED293DF8D9FE210E514EB2" blockId="3.[151,605,475,502]" box="[151,605,475,502]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<heading id="D0D781C5FFED293DF8D9FE210E514EB2" bold="true" box="[151,605,475,502]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DF8D9FE210E514EB2" bold="true" box="[151,605,475,502]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Key to species of genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DF9F3FE210E514EB2" authorityName="Harring" authorityYear="1913" box="[445,605,475,502]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DF9F3FE210E514EB2" bold="true" box="[445,605,475,502]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Philodinavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30D42E0CFFED293DF8D9FDDA09904D17" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFED293DF8D9FDDA09904D72" blockId="3.[151,1437,544,713]" box="[151,1436,544,566]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="30D1959CFFED293DF8D9FDDA09904D72" box="[151,1436,544,566]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
1a. With eyespots; spurs without an interspace; ramus with a median projection. 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DFB97FDDB09904D72" authority="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityName="Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone" authorityYear="2003" box="[985,1436,544,566]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="aussiensis">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DFB97FDDB085E4D72" box="[985,1106,545,566]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. aussiensis</emphasis>
Ricci, Shiel, Fontaneto &amp; Melone
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFED293DF8D9FDC709904D17" blockId="3.[151,1437,544,713]" box="[151,1436,573,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="30D1959CFFED293DF8D9FDC709904D17" box="[151,1436,573,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">1b. Without eyespots; spurs with an interspace; ramus without a median projection.................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D42E0CFFED293DF8D9FDA109914D8C" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFED293DF8D9FDA109914DCA" blockId="3.[151,1437,544,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="30D1959CFFED293DF8D9FDA109914DCA" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
2a. Ciliated buccal field single and with a pair of processes laterally; spurs thick or thin with a narrow or wide interspace........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DFC8FFD8309914DCA" authority="(Murray)" baseAuthorityName="Murray" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1217,1437,632,654]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DFC8FFD8309324DC9" box="[1217,1342,632,654]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. paradoxus</emphasis>
(Murray)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F36A9FFED293DF8D9FD6F09914D8C" blockId="3.[151,1437,544,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<keyLead id="30D1959CFFED293DF8D9FD6F09914D8C" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
2b. Two ciliated buccal fields separated by a septum and with a pair of thick and long processes as well as three pairs of small processes laterally; spurs thick and with a wide interspace....................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D2AFFED293DFCBAFD49096F4D8C" authority="Song &amp; Lee, 2022" authorityName="Song &amp; Lee" authorityYear="2022" box="[1268,1379,691,712]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinavidae" genus="Philodinavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="koreanus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B954EABBFFED293DFCBAFD49096F4D8C" box="[1268,1379,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. koreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26757C0FFED293DFD27FD4909914D8C" box="[1385,1437,691,712]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
